[[File:Jug detail.png|left|100px]]A '''Jug''' is an item that can be filled with [[water]] to create a [[jug of water]]. [[Jug of wine|Wine]] can also be made by adding [[grapes]] to a jug of water.

Jugs can be bought at [[general store]]s for one [[Coins|coin]] each. Jugs are not sold at the [[Catherby]], East Ardougne, or [[West Ardougne]] general store. However, jugs are sold by the charter crew members in Catherby. [[Wine Shop]] in [[Draynor Village]] sells them for the same price as the general stores, and they can be [[Thieving|thieved]] from the stall. [[Hassan]] at the [[Al Kharid]] palace may also give free jugs of water if the player has not completed [[Prince Ali Rescue]].

Jugs can also be found at their spawn points in the basement of [[Lumbridge Castle]], the [[Crafting Guild]], the [[Cooks' Guild]] (top floor), and some other kitchens.

Jugs can only be filled with water from [[sink]]s, [[fountain]]s and with the Lunar spell [[Humidify]]. They cannot be filled with water from [[well]]s; upon attempting to do so, a player receives the message "If I drop my jug down there, I don't think I'm likely to get it back." Also, jugs can be filled by filling another vessel with water and then using it on the jug (e.g. filling a [[bucket]] from a well, then using the [[BUCKET OF WATER|bucket of water]] on the jug).

